âThere is often an odour in her wisdom, as if it came forth from a
swamp.â âAlas! that I should have so long lived in the midst of their
noise and foul breath. O blessed stillness around me!â âO pure odours
around me!â âThat was the falsehood in my pity, that in each I saw and
smelt what was mind enough for him.... With blissful nostrils again I
