Nihilists, Sceptics, Ephectics, Hectics of the mind,â etc.

From these examples, the attentive reader must have already remarked
that the tumultuous rush of words frequently results from the merest
resemblance in sound. Not seldom does the riot of words degenerate
into paltry quibbling, into the silliest pun, into the automatic
association of words according to their sound, without regard to
their meaning. âIf this turn (_Wende_) in all the need (_Noth_) is
called necessity (_Nothwendigkeit_).â âThus ye boast (_brÃ¼stet_) of
yourselves--alas! even without breasts (_BrÃ¼ste_).â âThere is much
pious lick-spittle-work (_Speichel-Leckerie_), baking-of-flattery
(_Schmeichel-BÃ¤ckerei_) before the Lord of Hosts.â âSpit upon the
great town, which is the great slum (_Abraum_), where all the scum
(_Abschaum_) froths together (_zusammanschÃ¤umt_).â âHere and there
there is nothing to better (_bessern_), nothing to worsen (_bÃ¶sern_).â
âWhat have they to do there, far-seeing (weitsichtige), far-seeking
(_weit-sÃ¼chtige_) eyes?â âIn such processions (_ZÃ¼gen_) goats
(_Ziegen_) and geese, and the strong-headed and the wrong-headed
(_Kreuz und QuerkÃ¶pfe_), were always running on before.... O,
Will, turn of all need (_Wende aller Noth_)! O thou my necessity
(_Nothwendigkeit_)!â âThus I look afar over the creeping and swarming
of little gray waves (_Wellen_) and wills (_Willen_).â âThis seeking
(_Suchen_) for my home was the visitation (_Heimsuchung_) of me.â
âDid not the world become perfect, round and ripe (_reif_)? O for the
golden round ring (_Reif_)!â âYawns (_Klafft_) the abyss here too?
Yelps (_KlÃ¤fft_) the dog of hell here too?â âIt stultifies, brutalizes
(_verthiert_), and transforms into a bull (_verstiert_).â âLife is at
least (_mindestens_), at the mildest (_mildestens_), an exploiting.â
âWhom I deemed transformed akin to myself (_verwandt-verwandelt_),â etc.

Nietzsche, in the wild hurry of his thought, many a time fails to
comprehend the scintillating word-images elaborated in his centres of
speech; his consciousness, as it were, hears wrongly, misses its aim in
interpreting, and invents wondrous neologisms, which sound like known
expressions, but have no sort of fellowship in meaning with these. He
speaks, for example, of _Hinterweltlern_ (inhabitants of remote worlds)
from _HinterwÃ¤ldlern_ (backwoodsmen), of a _Kesselbauche_ (kettleâs
belly) when he is thinking of _Kesselpauche_ (kettledrum), etc.; or he
even repeats, as his centres of speech prompt, wholly incomprehensible,
meaningless sounds. âThen I went to the door: Alpa! I cried, who is
carrying his ashes to the mountain? Alpa! Alpa! who is carrying his
ashes to the mountain?â

He frequently associates his ideas, not according to the sound of the
word, but according to the similarity or habitual contiguity of the
concepts; then there arise âanalogousâ intellection and the fugitive
ideation, in which, to use Griesingerâs expression, he ârambles
incoherently from one topic to another.â Speaking of the âascetic
ideal,â _e.g._, he elaborates the idea that strong and noble spirits
take refuge in the desert, and, without any connection, adds: âOf
course, too, they would not want for camels there.â The representation
of the desert has irresistibly drawn after it the representation
of camels, habitually associated with it. At another time he says:
âBeasts of prey and men of prey, _e.g._, CÃ¦sar Borgia, are radically
misunderstood; Nature is misunderstood so long as a fundamental
diseased condition is sought for in these healthiest of all tropical
monsters and growths. It seems that there is among moralists a hatred
against the primeval forest and against the tropics, and that the
tropical man must, at any price, be discredited. But why? For the
benefit of the temperate zone? For the benefit of the temperate
(moderate) men? Of the mediocre?â In this case the contemplation of
CÃ¦sar Borgia forces upon him the comparison with a beast of prey; this
makes him think of the tropics, the torrid zone; from the torrid zone
he comes to the temperate zone, from this to the âtemperateâ man, and,
through the similarity of sound, to the âmediocreâ man (in German,
_gemÃ¤ssigt_ and _mittelmÃ¤ssig_).

âIn truth nothing remains of the world but green twilight and green
lightnings. Do as it pleases ye, ye wantons ... shake your emeralds
down into the deepest depth.â The quite incomprehensible âemeraldsâ
are called up into consciousness by the representation of the âgreenâ
twilight and lightnings.

In this and hundreds of other cases the course of ideation can, to a
certain extent, be followed, because all the links in the chain of
association are preserved. It often happens, however, that some of
these links are suppressed, and then there occur leaps of thought,
incomprehensible, and, consequently, bewildering to the reader: âIt
was the body who despaired of the earth, who heard the belly of being
