too many about me,â so thinks the hermit. One times one to infinity at
last makes two!â âWhat, then, do they call that which makes them proud?
They name it culture; it distinguishes them from the goat-herds.â

Finally, the connection of the associated representations suddenly
snaps, and he breaks off in the midst of a sentence to begin a new one:
âFor in religion the passions have once more rights of citizenship,
