expressed, âI say Yes to water.â Instead of âI am sleepy,â he would
say, âI say Nay to wakefulness,â or, âI say Yes to bed,â etc. This is
the way in which invalids in incomplete aphasia are in the habit of
paraphrasing their thoughts.

